narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Not particularly exciting, but it isn't horrible. I would say that I enjoyed it for the most part.

French 130 is basically a review and extension of 110 and 120. It's not a very riveting course, but the books and films that we watch and discuss are way more interesting that Mireille and Robert of 110/120.

Yes, French 130 is one of the more challenging language classes that I've taken, relative to L1/L2 but you also gain so much from it. It's challenging, but definitely manageable and you'll walk away from it being able to read real French literature!
I would describe it as intense yet extremely fulfilling.Yes I would, because it focuses on the building blocks of the language that we often take for granted.
I would definitely recommend this course. It was a really important and in-depth review of key grammar concepts that I needed. We also read some cool books.
I would recommend this course to anyone who's taken French in high school but would like to make sure they've got the language basics down.
I would definitely recommend this class! You learn so much about French, especially if your French teachers in high school only covered the basics.
One learns a multitude of verb tenses and expands/emphasizes on previously learned grammar and verb tenses.
A CLASS WHERE I READ CAMUS AND OTHER FRENCH OUVRES.I ALSO TRIED TO MASTER GRAMMAR SKILLS.
